text: Outey I (1672-1696), also known as Udayaraja II or Narai Ramathipadi II, born Ang Yong (), was the Cambodian king reigned from 1695 to 1696. Outey I was a son of Kaev Hua II. He succeeded the king after his uncle Chey Chettha IV's first abdication. He reigned only ten months, died suddenly. Chey Chettha IV then regained power. ==References== * Achille Dauphin-Meunier Histoire du Cambodge P.U.F Paris 1968. Category:1672 births Category:1696 deaths Category:17th-century Cambodian monarchs
